# NOTE: Keep this list short (~8 entries). Remove old ones as new ones land.
CHANGELOG = [
    "b412: in-game Tourist mode (type 'tourist' as your name) gains a starting-depth picker. After the playtest_mode activation banner, a new tourist_depth screen offers 12 preset chips (F1, F5, F10, F15, F20, F25, F30, F35, F40, F45, F49, F50) with one-line blurbs explaining why each band matters for testing. Picking F>1 warps the maxed-out Playtester to that floor by generating F2..F<N> on demand and pre-discovering F1..F<N-1>, so the player can still retreat up the stairs to earlier vendors without re-exploring fog. F1 short-circuits the warp. Refactor: factored the harness's _generate_floors_and_plant_at out of playtest_harness.py into a shared game_systems.plant_player_at_depth(); the harness now thin-wraps the shared helper, and the new in-game picker reuses the same code path. Also bumps gs.game_stats['max_floor_reached'] so depth achievements count the plant. No effect on non-Tourist character creation -- regular names still flow name -> race -> gender -> sprite -> cantrips/shop unchanged.",
    "b411: Zot's Guardian victory trigger + caster build for the boss fight. End-game smoke test (9 seeds, F50 plant with all 8 shards) found 4 bugs blocking the final encounter: (1) the victory_screen trigger at combat.py:1075 was nested inside `if not runes_obtained['battle']` AND `if is_legendary` -- neither holds when a player arrives at F50 with all 8 shards (battle rune long since collected) AND the Guardian doesn't have is_legendary set. Melee-killing the boss flowed silently to combat_victory and the YOU WIN screen never fired. Patched all three kill paths (melee at combat.py:1180, channeled-spell at 750, instant-cast-spell at 1900) to capture is_zots_guardian before clearing active_monster and trigger victory_screen directly. (2) Plant baseline now memorizes non-resisted damage spells (Mind Blast Psionic L3 / Earthquake Earth L3 / Holy Smite Holy L4 / Psychic Scream Psionic L4) at F30+/F35+; without them the Guardian (resists Physical/Fire/Ice/Lightning/Light/Darkness) ate the entire Inferno / Meteor Strike / Flame Lance / Lightning Bolt core suite at 0.5x effective damage. (3) Surface elemental_strength / elemental_weakness on monster obs and damage_type on spell obs; the smart-policy damage picker (spell_casting_mode position 6 + burst-nuke 1b) now scores by resistance-adjusted base_power so a Fire spell against a Fire-resistant target loses to a Mind Blast. (4) Boss-combat overrides: skip Spectral Hand / Stone Skin recasts (they drain mana on long fights) and disable all flee triggers when fighting the Guardian (the boss arena has no re-engagement path, fleeing locks the agent in a stairs_down_mode loop on the bottom-of-dungeon cap). Result: 9/9 seeds beat Zot's Guardian -- dwarves 52-55T (pure melee), elves 105-125T (Holy Smite cycle), humans 143-150T. Also extends b410's repair perimeter (Rune of Growth, warp gates) so the natural quest path can both START and FINISH.",
    "b410: repair the Rune of Growth path so the 8-Shard quest can complete + gate-lock the warp paths so it can't be skipped. Audit (post-b409) of all 8 rune triggers found Growth was a dead end: room_actions.py:2547 was a literal `pass` stub for the World Tree harvest, gs.rune_progress['gardens_harvested_total'] was never incremented anywhere despite the 75-harvest req in rune_progress_reqs, and gs.world_tree_available was never set True so the G-room upgrade at game_systems.py:2479 never fired. Without Growth the gate_to_floor_50_unlocked check (game_systems.py:4481) could never pass and F50 was unreachable. Three patches: (1) increment gardens_harvested_total on every garden harvest (room_actions.py:2633), trigger 'A primordial sapling has taken root...' announcement + flag flip at >= 75. (2) Replace the World Tree harvest stub with a proper Rune-of-Growth award (verdant rune, growth shard vault unlock), mirroring the Codex / Champion patterns. (3) b409 follow-up: clamp ALL deep-floor entry paths (warp 1 / warp 2 / Zot's Key / Scroll of Descent) at F49 when gate_to_floor_50_unlocked is False, so a random portal roll or Scroll of Descent on F47-F49 can no longer skip the 8-Shard quest by depositing the player directly onto the boss arena. The stair descent from F49 was already gated; this completes the perimeter and restores the design-intent quest path: 75 harvested gardens -> World Tree spawns -> harvest = Rune of Growth -> shard vault spawn -> all 8 shards -> Gate to F50 opens -> face Zot's Guardian.",
    "b409: cap dungeon at F50 (z=49) in stairs descent + warp paths. b408 deploy sweep caught elf seed=12 reaching max_floor=51 -- past the designed boss-arena cap. Two cap-check holes patched: (1) handle_stairs_down (game_systems.py:4267) bumped player_character.z += 1 unconditionally, so an agent already on F50 with a D tile descended into a generated F51. Now refuses descent from F50 with 'You stand at the bottom of the cavern. There is nowhere deeper to descend.' (2) handle_warp_room's overwhelmed-by-portal branch (line 4344) computed max_z = z + 2 without the MAX_FLOOR_Z = 49 clamp that the other warp at line 3037 already had. Now mirrors that pattern: max_z = min(MAX_FLOOR_Z, z + 2). Both Zot's Dimensional Key (room_actions.py:4097) and Scroll of Descent (items.py:2028) already capped at z=49, so this completes the perimeter. The F50 mission to reach the cap remains intact -- only the post-F50 phantom generation is closed.",
    "b408: High-tier damage spells + burst-nuke priority for casters. b407 lifted caster F25 survival to 37-40% but Inferno / Meteor Strike were memorized but barely cast (audit: 70 of 6260 total spell casts across 40 caster runs were L3+ damage). The spell_casting_mode priority cascade had damage at position 6 behind Hold Monster -> Spectral Hand -> Mage Armor -> Stone Skin; the 3 buff turns burned through monster swings that landed status-lockout (Frost Worm freeze, Basilisk paralysis, Gorgon petrify) before damage ever fired. Two coordinated changes: (1) added Meteor Strike (L3, 45 base / 22 MP, ~79 dmg at F25 elf) and Inferno (L4, 55 base / 35 MP, ~94 dmg) to the F18+ / F22+ memorize tier list, dropped Minor Heal / Fireball / Battle Hymn / Purify from the F20+ list to free slot budget (Battle Hymn confirmed by b403 audit as never auto-cast; Purify duplicates inventory Antidote; Minor Heal superseded by Heal/Greater/Mass). (2) Added a burst-nuke gate at priority position 1b (right after Hold Monster, before Spectral Hand): if best affordable damage spell is L3+ AND base_power x 2 >= monster max_hp, fire it instead of buff cascade. Two Meteor Strike casts (~158 dmg net) drop a 150-HP F25 monster faster than 3 buffs + 2 attacks, AND skip the buff-cast channel-init swings that land status-lockout. Audit verification: Meteor Strike casts 13 -> 24 (+85%), Inferno 57 -> 83 (+45%). Final F25-plant sweep (3000T, 30 seeds): dwarf 21/30 (70%, avg max F34.7), elf 16/30 (53%, F31.1, max F39), human 13/30 (43%, F29.9, F39). Elf gained +6 alive seeds over b407.",
    "b407: F25-plant probes the F30-F50 wall + caster combat wedge fix. The user's directive was 'stronger F25 plants to find and break the F30-F50 wall'. Baseline (b406, 1500T, 30 seeds, F25 plant): dwarf 3/30 (avg max F26.8), elf 10/30 (F25.2), human 3/30 (F25.4) -- plants died too fast on F25 to even probe the F30 wall, and the smart-policy descent gate (line 6260, weakly_geared_d = (eq_w+eq_a) < (2*z+3)) refused descent at F25 since maxed starter Dagger+Leather can't clear 53. Six coordinated changes turned plant strength up enough to expose the real wall: (1) target_level N-2 -> N+1 (F25 plant L23 -> L26), (2) elixir_bonus N//5 -> N//4 (F25 +5 -> +6 each stat), (3) upg (N-1)//3 -> (N-1)//2 (F25 +8 -> +12 with cap from weapon's upgrade_limit), (4) gear swap by tier: F15+ Adamantine Sword + Dragon Scale, F20+ Volcanic Blade + Volcanic Mail, F25+ Enchanted Longsword + Enchanted Plate -- at F25 the gear bar lands at 76 (vs 53 threshold), descent gate clears, (5) Tier 6 inventory at F25+: Antidote x3 (cure_all), Master Healing Potion x3 extra, Restoration Scroll x2, Teleport Scroll x2, Bratwurst x6 (sausages don't rot, outlasts the 7000T food clock), (6) base_max_health_bonus += (N-1)*5 and base_max_mana_bonus += (N-1)*3 (F25 elf 290 -> 410 HP, 270 -> 342 MP) -- the b407 death audit showed status-lockout (Frost Worm freeze, Basilisk paralysis, Gorgon petrify) killed casters in 2-3 swings of 50-80 dmg without an HP buffer to absorb. Bonus bug fixes: (a) wedge-break in combat_mode was returning 'x' (combat.py:1271 rejects 'x' as 'Invalid combat command'); F25 elf seed=4 burned 2919 turns firing invalid 'x' against a Werewolf because Mage Armor / Stone Skin buffs don't change HP / kills / position so freeze_streak hit 30. Now returns 'f' for combat_mode wedge-trips. (b) freeze_key now includes mana so a caster buffing themselves in combat counts as world progress and doesn't trip the wedge. Final 3000T sweep (30 seeds, F25 plant): dwarf 21/30 (70%, avg max F34.7, max F41), elf 11/30 (37%, F30.5, F39), human 12/30 (40%, F29.1, F37). The F30-F50 wall is visible: dwarves hit it around F40-F41, casters around F35-F39, F25-F30 transition still claims many casters via status-lockout monsters and big-hit elites (Death Knight 90 dmg, Demilich 98 dmg, Storm Giant 72 dmg + Burn).",
    "b405: Spectral Hand + Mage Armor toned down. The b404 sweep correctly broke the F25 caster wall but went too far: F25 elf 24/30 (80%) and F25 human 21/30 (70%) survived vs F25 dwarf 8/30 (27%), inverting the intended caster=glass-cannon / dwarf=tank archetype. Two targeted nerfs: (1) Spectral Hand 3-absorb / 8-turn / 14 MP -> 1-absorb / 4-turn / 16 MP. Was effectively erasing ~240 raw F25 damage per cast (3 hits * ~80 dmg/swing); now it's a single-absorb insurance card for one critical hit, with shorter window and higher mana cost. (2) Mage Armor +6 DEF / 10 turns -> +4 DEF / 6 turns. Combined with Stone Skin's +8 DEF for 4 turns, casters were stacking +14 DEF which made F25 hits effectively single-digit. Now +12 DEF stacked (still strong, but enemies land 3-4x more damage). Both spells remain mana-efficient defensive options -- Mage Armor still 3 DEF-turns per MP, beating Stone Skin's 1.78. Target after b405: casters land in the 25-45% F25 survival band, dwarf martial baseline (27%) competitive. Pre-combat buff casting (the b404 wishlist item) intentionally NOT added -- F25 numbers were already too high.",
    "b404: fix spell priority + monster obs in spell_casting_mode + Talisman as random drop. b403 audit (18 caster seeds across F15/F25) revealed three bugs that left the new caster suite essentially inactive: (1) Hold Monster cast 0 times across all 18 audit runs because Stone Skin was first in the spell_casting_mode cascade and always fired when defense_boost wasn't active -- Hold Monster never reached. (2) Mage Armor and Spectral Hand never cast either, for the same priority-order reason. (3) F25 elf hit the 24-slot memorize cap before Spectral Hand could be added (Mage Armor + Spectral Hand were at the tail of the tier list, dropped when the slot budget ran out). (4) _monster_obs returned None outside combat_mode, so the spell_casting_mode tough_fight gate (m_max_hp >= 30% pc max) always evaluated False even when the policy correctly transitioned modes. Six coordinated fixes: rewrote spell_casting_mode priority to Hold Monster -> Spectral Hand -> Mage Armor -> Stone Skin -> Heal -> Damage (Stone Skin no longer fires first); each defensive layer now gates on its own status_effect_name rather than the shared 'defense_boost' effect_type, so Mage Armor + Stone Skin can stack for +14 DEF; reordered _grant_memorized_spells tier list to put Mage Armor / Spectral Hand BEFORE Battle Hymn + Purify so the F25 24-slot budget actually fits them; surfaced gs.active_monster in spell_casting_mode obs; removed the b403 Hourglass Talisman auto-grant from plant baseline and added it to UNIQUE_TREASURE_TEMPLATES (level 4) so it spawns via the same 10%-chest / vault-reward path as Heartstone Pendant + Wizard's Monocle. Audit verification (18 seeds): F25 elf went from 0/18 surviving (b403) to 14/18 (78%); F25 human 0 -> 11/18 (61%). Hold Monster cast 47-49% of all casts; Mage Armor and Spectral Hand each active ~35 turns per run.",
]
